-- Citigroup shares fall below $2 as U.S. banks plummet
-- 
-- Fri Feb 20, 2009 9:53am EST
-- http://www.reuters.com/article/2009/02/20/us-markets-stocks-banks-idUSTRE51J3OH20090220

 

 NEW YORK  (Reuters) - Shares of Citigroup ( C.N ) dropped more than 20 percent to fall below $2 as bank shares plummeted shortly after the opening bell on Friday on fears the U.S. bank rescue plan might include nationalization. 

 Bank of America ( BAC.N ) fell more than 15 percent to $3.31 and Wells Fargo ( WFC.N ) tumbled more than 12 percent while JP Morgan ( JPM.N ) shed 5.8 percent. The Financial Select Sector SPDR ( XLF.P ) fell 4.5 percent to $7.22. (Editing by  James Dalgleish )